member.example:
This sample shows how to call CreateOrUpdateWidgetAsync with required parameters and request content, and how to parse the result.

var client = new WidgetManagerClient();

var data = new {
    manufacturerId = "<manufacturerId>",
};

var operation = await client.CreateOrUpdateWidgetAsync(WaitUntil.Completed, "<widgetName>", RequestContent.Create(data));

BinaryData data = operation.Value;
JsonElement result = JsonDocument.Parse(data.ToStream()).RootElement;
Console.WriteLine(result.GetProperty("name").ToString());
Console.WriteLine(result.GetProperty("manufacturerId").ToString());

This sample shows how to call CreateOrUpdateWidgetAsync with all parameters and request content, and how to parse the result.

var client = new WidgetManagerClient();

var data = new {
    manufacturerId = "<manufacturerId>",
    sharedModel = new {
        tag = "<tag>",
        createdDate = "2022-05-10T14:57:31.2311892-04:00",
    },
};

var operation = await client.CreateOrUpdateWidgetAsync(WaitUntil.Completed, "<widgetName>", RequestContent.Create(data));

BinaryData data = operation.Value;
JsonElement result = JsonDocument.Parse(data.ToStream()).RootElement;
Console.WriteLine(result.GetProperty("name").ToString());
Console.WriteLine(result.GetProperty("manufacturerId").ToString());
Console.WriteLine(result.GetProperty("sharedModel").GetProperty("tag").ToString());
Console.WriteLine(result.GetProperty("sharedModel").GetProperty("createdDate").ToString());

member.remarks:
Below is the JSON schema for the request and response payloads.

Request Body:

Schema for Widget:
{
  name: string, # Required.
  manufacturerId: string, # Required.
  sharedModel: {
    tag: string, # Required.
    createdDate: string (date & time), # Required.
  }, # Optional.
}


Response Body:

Schema for Widget:
{
  name: string, # Required.
  manufacturerId: string, # Required.
  sharedModel: {
    tag: string, # Required.
    createdDate: string (date & time), # Required.
  }, # Optional.
}

